Care Tips: Use healthy, disease-free seed rhizomes, plant on raised beds or ridges, maintain mulch,
apply NPK and organic manures in splits, and manage rhizome rot and foliar diseases.
Best Weather: Warm, humid weather with well-distributed rains followed by a dry period at harvest.
Cost Profit Note: High-value spice crop with good economic returns where price, yield, and curing
